## Our Verdict

**Rating: ★★★★★ 4.7/5**

The Hypervolt Home 3 Pro is the charger we'd recommend to anyone who wants the full package. It looks fantastic, it's built like a tank, and it offers a feature set that covers virtually every use case: solar integration without extra hardware, smart tariff support for both Octopus and OVO, dynamic load management, and an app that's genuinely a pleasure to use.

The premium price is the main barrier. At ~£1,300 installed, it's roughly £300–£500 more than the [Ohme Home Pro](/reviews/ohme-home-pro-review/) or [Pod Point Solo 3](/reviews/pod-point-solo-3-review/). If you're purely focused on smart tariff savings and don't have solar panels, the Ohme remains better value for money. And if solar is your sole priority, the [myenergi Zappi](/reviews/zappi-v2-review/) still edges it with dedicated Eco+ mode and existing battery storage support.

But as an all-rounder that combines the best of both worlds — smart tariff support *and* excellent solar integration — in a package that genuinely enhances your home's kerb appeal? Nothing else comes close.

**Buy the Hypervolt Home 3 Pro if:** You want the best-looking charger with no feature compromises. Ideal for solar panel owners who also want smart tariff integration. Perfect if you value UK-made quality and future-proof design.

**Look elsewhere if:** Budget is your primary concern — the [Ohme Home Pro](/reviews/ohme-home-pro-review/) delivers excellent smart tariff savings for less. If you need an untethered charger, the Hypervolt doesn't offer a socketed option.

