## Frequently Asked Questions

### Is the Hypervolt Home 3 Pro compatible with Intelligent Octopus Go?

Yes. The Hypervolt Home 3 Pro is fully compatible with Intelligent Octopus Go. Connect it through the Octopus app, set your departure time and desired charge level, and the system will automatically schedule charging during the cheapest off-peak slots — typically 6–8p/kWh overnight. It also supports OVO Charge Anytime, which many competitors don't.

### Does the Hypervolt Home 3 Pro work with solar panels?

Yes — solar integration is built in with no extra hardware required. The charger offers three modes: Boost (full power, grid + solar), Eco (solar priority with grid backup), and Super Eco (solar only). A CT clamp monitors your home's energy usage in real time. See our [solar panels and EV charging guide](/guides/ev-charger-solar-panels-uk/) for more.

### What is party mode on the Hypervolt?

Party mode is a fun LED light feature that cycles through rainbow colours on the charger's front light ring while charging. You can enable it through the Hypervolt app. It's purely cosmetic and can be turned off or dimmed if it's not your thing — but it's become something of a cult favourite among Hypervolt owners.

### Is the Hypervolt Home 3 Pro worth the premium price?

For solar panel owners, we'd say absolutely — the built-in three-mode solar integration saves you the cost of buying a separate accessory (like the Easee Equalizer at ~£224). For non-solar users on a tight budget, the [Ohme Home Pro](/reviews/ohme-home-pro-review/) offers similar smart tariff features at a lower price. But if you want the best build quality, design, and feature set in one charger, the Hypervolt justifies the premium.

### Do I need an earth rod for the Hypervolt Home 3 Pro?

No. The Hypervolt Home 3 Pro includes built-in PEN fault protection, so no separate earth rod is needed. This simplifies installation and keeps things looking tidy.

